Reason:
The bug occurs because the hop limit from a router advertisement (RA) can overwrite a higher hop limit set for the interface, allowing an attacker to set a low hop limit that could cause legitimate packets to be dropped. This happens when the hop limit from the RA is directly assigned to the interface's configuration without any checks.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```c
if (in6_dev->cnf.hop_limit < ra_msg->icmph.icmp6_hop_limit) {
